text: Actinodaphne montana is a species of plant in the family Lauraceae. It is a tree endemic to Peninsular Malaysia. The Latin specific epithet montana refers to mountains or coming from mountains.Archibald William Smith ==References== montana Category:Endemic flora of Peninsular Malaysia Category:Trees of Peninsular Malaysia Category:Least concern plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Plants described in 1910
